The paper discusses the history and future of Artificial Intelligence (AI), which is a subfield of Computer Science (CS). The paper specifically mentions the theoretical foundations of AI, embodied agents, and self-referential problem solvers, which are all topics that fall under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions probability theory, which is commonly used in machine learning and falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The discussion of embodied agents and hardware speedups suggests a focus on robotics and control, which fall under the categories of Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the mention of self-referential problem solvers suggests a focus on programming languages and formal methods, which fall under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL).
